message.content: Opuntia engelmannii is a species of cactus native to the southwestern United States and northern Mexico. It typically has a shrubby growth habit and can reach heights of up to three meters. The cactus pads are oblong to circular in shape, with a waxy texture and a green to bluish-green color. They are covered in a dense layer of long, sharp spines that are typically yellow in color. The flowers of Opuntia engelmannii are a bright yellow color and bloom in the spring or early summer. This species of cactus can be found in a variety of habitats, including rocky canyons, desert washes, and grasslands. It is cultivated as an ornamental plant as well as for its edible fruits, which are commonly referred to as prickly pears.
